	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-03T03:44:49">Ladbrokes plc is engaged in the betting and gaming industry. The Company has approximately 2,700 betting outlets in the United Kingdom, Ireland, Belgium and Spain. Its segments include UK Retail, European Retail, Digital, Core Telephone Betting and High Rollers. The UK Retail segment comprises betting activities in the shop estate in Great Britain. The European Retail segment comprises all activities connected with the Ireland (Northern and Republic of), Belgium and Spain shop estates. The Digital segment comprises betting and gaming activities from online and mobile operations, which includes Ladbrokes Israel, Ladbrokes Australia and Betdaq. The Core Telephone Betting segment comprises activities relating to bets taken on the telephone, excluding High Rollers. The High Rollers segment comprises activities primarily relating to bets taken on the telephone by High Rollers.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-23T14:39:43">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 31 December 2015, Ladbrokes PLC revenues increased 2% to L1.2B. Net income decreased 88% to L5.1M. Revenues reflect an increase in demand for the Company's products and services due to favorable market conditions. Net income was offset by Before exceptional depreciation increase of 25% to L71.4M (expense), Exceptional-Depreciation increase of 72% to L27.9M (expense).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
